# Vocalo Chord Assistant — Project Rules

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript strict, Tailwind CSS, Zustand
- Audio: Tone.js + smplr (lazy-loaded, shared AudioContext)
- Deploy: Vercel

## Design System (Vocacore Theme)
- All colors use `voca-*` Tailwind tokens. NEVER use slate, gray, zinc, neutral.
- bg-voca-bg (#0D0D14), bg-voca-bg-card (#16162A), bg-voca-bg-section (#1E1E3A), bg-voca-bg-elevated (#222244)
- accent-cyan (#00E5FF), accent-magenta (#E040FB), accent-purple (#7C4DFF)
- text-voca-text (#F0F0F8), text-voca-text-sub (#8888AA), text-voca-text-muted (#7C7C9C)
- Primary buttons: bg-voca-accent-cyan text-voca-bg font-bold rounded-lg
- Cards: bg-voca-bg-card border border-voca-border-subtle rounded-xl
- Active/selected: border-voca-accent-cyan shadow-glow-cyan

## Code Standards
- No `any` type. No `@ts-ignore`. Strict TypeScript.
- All audio/browser API access must be inside useEffect or async functions (SSR safety).
- Components using browser APIs must be imported with `dynamic(() => import(...), { ssr: false })`.
- Report in Japanese when summarizing changes.

## Commands
- `npm run build`: Build
- `npm run lint`: Lint
- `npx tsc --noEmit`: Type check
- All three must pass with 0 errors, 0 warnings before committing.
